SUMMARY:Be My Neighbor Day
DESCRIPTION:Join PBS KVIE for Be My Neighbor Day on Saturday\, April 11\, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Be My Neighbor Day is a free family event that builds on the values and themes presented in Daniel Tiger’s Neighborhood and focuses on early learning and the importance of being a caring neighbor. \n  \nReturning for its second year\, the event will feature hands-on activities that celebrate community. Attendees can enjoy Daniel Tiger-themed crafts\, write thank-you letters to community helpers\, and get up close with first responder vehicles – collecting stamps from around the event to win PBS KIDS prizes. Guests will also have a chance to meet Daniel Tiger from PBS KIDS’ Daniel Tiger’s Neighborhood! \n  \nRegistration\, which is free but required\, opens on March 5. Visit the Be My Neighbor Day webpage at kvie.org/neighbor to register\, get more information\, and sign up for email updates. Be My Neighbor Day is supported by PNC Grow Up Great and SCOE Early Learning and presented in partnership with Fred Rogers Productions. Additional support is provided by Child Action\, SMUD\, Kaiser Permanente\, and Shriners Children’s Northern California. \n  \nWHERE: \nPBS KVIE \n2030 W. El Camino Avenue \nSacramento\, CA 95833-1866 \n  \nWHEN: \nSaturday\, April 11\, 10 a.m. – 2 p.m. \n  \nADMISSION: \nFree\, but registration is required \n  \nWEBSITE: \nkvie.org/neighbor
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/be-my-neighbor-day/
LOCATION:PBS KVIE\, 2030 W. El Camino Avenue\, Sacramento\, CA\, 95833
CATEGORIES:Bring the Kids,Community
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/PBS-KVIE-BMND-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
