SUMMARY:Natural Wine Tasting
DESCRIPTION:🚲🍷Black Bicycle Farm Natural Wine Tasting 🍷🚲\nSaturday\, April 11 | 12:00–5:00 pm \nReady to taste wine with a little wild streak? \nStep into the expressive\, anything-but-ordinary world of Black Bicycle Farm at Great Bear Vineyards. This guided natural wine tasting is a deep dive into wines made from organically grown grapes\, crafted with minimal intervention and maximum personality—where the vineyard\, vintage\, and nature itself take center stage. \n✨ What to Expect:\n• A guided tasting of five distinct natural wines\, each with its own story\n• A chance to explore orange wine\, unfiltered whites\, and playful carbonic reds\n• Insight into the philosophy\, creativity\, and artistry behind natural winemaking \n🍇 Featured Wines:\n• Squiggle 2023 – Bold\, structured orange wine layered with citrus and textured depth\n• Orange Tipple 2023 – Perfumed with elderflower\, vibrant apricot\, honey\, and orange notes\n• Clash of the Titans 2022 – Cabernet Sauvignon–Zinfandel blend with harmonious red and dark fruit\n• After the Fire 2020 – Cabernet Sauvignon harvested during the 2020 wildfires; smoky\, spicy\, and unforgettable\n• Carbo Cab 2019 – Playful\, unfiltered Cabernet bursting with Bing cherry and candied strawberry\, lifted by carbonic maceration \nSet against the rustic elegance of our winery\, this tasting celebrates innovation\, sustainability\, and letting nature do the talking—guided by people who are genuinely passionate about the craft. \nWhether you’re a longtime natural wine fan or simply curious to try something new\, this is a tasting that promises to be thought-provoking\, delicious\, and full of character. \n🎟 Tickets required. Come sip outside the box with us!
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/natural-wine-tasting/
LOCATION:Great Bear Vineyards (Great Bear)\, 24800 County Rd 101A
CATEGORIES:Food & Drink
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/4-11-26-Thumbnail.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Great Bear Vineyards":MAILTO:greatbearvineyards@gmail.com
GEO:38.5818013;-121.7499687
