SUMMARY:Music for Natalie!
DESCRIPTION:The Davis Odd Fellows is once again hosting Music for Natalie! This annual event celebrates the life of Davis Police Officer Natalie Corona\, killed in the line of duty on January 10th\, 2019. This event also raises awareness for the Officer Natalie Corona Odd Fellows Memorial Scholarship\, awarded annually to graduating High School Seniors from High Schools in Davis and Pierce High in Arbuckle who are going into careers in law enforcement or first responders. \nThe 8th annual event will be held Saturday\, April 11th\, 2026 from 12-5 p.m. in Downtown Davis at the G Street Plaza. The event is free and open to all ages and there will be live music\, food vendors\, and beverages. Event details and scholarship applications can be found at davislodge.org under the ‘Programs’ tab. We hope to see you there!
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/music-for-natalie/
LOCATION:G Street Plaza\, Davis\, CA
CATEGORIES:Community
ORGANIZER;CN="Davis Odd Fellows":MAILTO:davislodge@sbcglobal.net
END:VEVENT
