SUMMARY:Two for the Price of One: Natural Wine Tasting
DESCRIPTION:🍷🚲 Natural Wine Tasting — Two for the Price of One! 🚲🍷\nSaturday\, April 11 | 12–5pm\nReady to sip something a little different? Step into the vibrant world of Black Bicycle Farm’s natural wines at Great Bear Vineyards—where creativity\, sustainability\, and a little bit of wild magic come together in every glass. ✨\nThis Saturday only: Bring a friend. Buy one ticket. Taste together.\n🚲 Ride your bike to the winery OR\n🧺 Stop by the Davis Farmers Market first\n…then show us your wheels or your market receipt and your friend tastes FREE!\nMake a day of it—grab some fresh bread\, cheese\, or picnic treats from the market and enjoy them at the vineyard while you sip. Honestly\, there are few better ways to spend a Saturday in Yolo County. 🌿🍷\n🍇 What to Expect:\nA guided tasting of five unique natural wines\nExplore orange wines\, unfiltered whites\, and playful reds\nLearn about the artistry of low-intervention winemaking\nDiscover wines that truly reflect the vineyard and vintage\n🍷 Featured Wines Include:\nSquiggle 2023 — bold orange wine with citrus and texture\nOrange Tipple 2023 — floral\, apricot\, honey\, and orange notes\nClash of the Titans 2022 — Cab-Zin blend bursting with fruit\nAfter the Fire 2020 — smoky\, spicy Cabernet with a story to tell\nCarbo Cab 2019 — light\, lively\, and delightfully playful\nSet against the rustic charm of the vineyard\, this is your chance to explore innovation\, sustainability\, and seriously fun wines—whether you’re a natural wine enthusiast or just curious to try something new.\nTwo people. One ticket. This Saturday only.\nGrab your friend and join us!
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/two-for-the-price-of-one-natural-wine-tasting/
LOCATION:Great Bear Vineyards (Great Bear)\, 24800 County Rd 101A
CATEGORIES:Food & Drink
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/4-11-26-BOGO-Thumbnail.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Great Bear Vineyards":MAILTO:greatbearvineyards@gmail.com
GEO:38.5818013;-121.7499687
